The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 01 October is 393,931 (699.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 27 September, there were 32,656 new confirmed cases (58.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 20 September, there were 26,303 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 24% (6353 extra cases).
